        <odd id="ref7">
            <head>African American History Note</head>
            <p>The account of Daphne Peterson, a freed African American, may be of particular interest.</p>
        </odd>
        <odd id="ref8">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>The Benjamin Rush memorandum book documents a variety of Rush's financial transactions and investments. The book often contains specific details on lands Rush owned in Pennsylvania. Other transactions recorded include payments to schoolmasters for his children and the loans of books he made to people.</p>
        </odd>
        <acqinfo id="ref5">
            <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition note</head>
            <p>Purchased from Romaine and accessioned, 1949.</p>
        </acqinfo>
        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Benjamin Rush was a physician, patriot, and humanitarian. He graduated from the College of New Jersey (Princeton), 1760, and from the University of Edinburgh, 1768. He was a member of the staff at the Pennsylvania Hospital and was a professor at the University of Pennsylvania.</p>
        </bioghist>
